Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/
Object: A model describing annotations added to procedure steps by the Indexing and Data Management Section of the House of Commons Library. Annotations are used to describe how a procedure step is actualised.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/linkNote
Object: A note that describes where a business item should link to in a publication.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/BusinessStep
Object: A business step is a step that can be actualised by a business item.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/scopeNote
Object: A note that describes the rules for actualising a business step.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/dateNote
Object: A note that describes the date to use when actualising a business step.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/actualiseWith
Object: Relates a business step to a business step where steps may be actualised together.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/procedure-step-annotation/source
Object: Relates a business step to the publication which is the source of information for that step.
